{"questionId":"9083121","questionHtml":"<p>What is the relationship between the resistivity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi></math> of a uniform wire, the radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> of the wire and the length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi></math> of the wire when its resistance is constant?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi><mo>∝</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi><mo>∝</mo><mi>r</mi><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi><mo>∝</mo><mfrac><mi>l</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi><mo>∝</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9083121","referenceCode":"20N.1A.SL.TZ0.16","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"What is the relationship between the resistivity ρ of a uniform wire, the radius r of the wire and the length l of the wire when its resistance is constant? A. ρ∝r2l B. ρ∝rl2 C. ρ∝","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"16","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["B. The particulate nature of matter","B.5 Current and circuits"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}